# Cloudrop Environment Configuration
# Copy this to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in the real API URL.
#
# REQUIRED: Backend API base URL
# The frontend will append /generate-upload-url, /save-link, /get-link/:id as needed.
#
# Examples:
#   - AWS API Gateway: https://your-api-id.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod
#   - Local development: http://localhost:3000
#   - Custom domain: https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# NOTE: This must point to YOUR backend. The frontend never needs AWS credentials.
# All AWS credentials must remain on the backend only.
VITE_API_URL=https://YOUR_API.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prod

# Debugging Tips:
# 1. If you see "Upload failed: Failed to get upload URL (404): Not Found"
#    - Check that VITE_API_URL is set correctly above
#    - Verify the backend endpoint /generate-upload-url exists
#    - Check browser DevTools Console for detailed logs (starting with [uploadFile])
#
# 2. For local development with a local backend on port 3000:
#    VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# 3. In Vercel production, set VITE_API_URL in:
#    Project Settings → Environment Variables
